items.title: Vegan Recipes That Don‚Äôt Suck
items.content_text:
The Book

I‚Äôm not sure why Denise got this from the library, neither one of us is vegan, but we have made several items and they have all been fantastic. Though the Overnight Chocolate Coffee Chia Pudding recipe is a little finicky‚Ä¶chia seeds need to be distributed equally among the jars or they won‚Äôt set properly. Anyway, recommended for any foodie‚Ä¶even if you favor meat like me. :)

The Food

After using the InstantPot to make up a bag of black beans we made black bean burgers and black bean enchiladas from the book‚Ä¶yummy!

items.title: Yeti Drinkware
items.content_text: It‚Äôs true I may have a bit of a problem, but I love my Yeti gear. I haven‚Äôt had any issues with their coolers, apparel, or drinkware‚Ä¶except for one. The Rambler 18oz bottle (2nd from left) is not great for coffee‚Ä¶it is just too messy. The ridge inside the bottle for the screw top causes coffee to go all over the place when pouring out‚Ä¶like into a small cup. OK, maybe I‚Äôm exaggerating a little bit, but coffee absolutely drips down the side and it is frustrating. So unless you drink straight from it, which for me would only be pleasurable with a cold drink, I don‚Äôt think it is as stellar as their other products. I have little doubt though that it will stop me from continuing to purchase their gear.
